        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 1:18AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 117 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Camp Creek State Park, or 10 miles north of Matoaka, moving east at
60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Athens...
Pipestem...
Camp Creek...
Camp Creek State Park...
Flat Top...
Jumping Branch...
and Pipestem Resort State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM EDT for
southwestern Virginia...and southeastern West Virginia.</instruction>
